description:
&lt;p&gt;Intermediate Care Service- Rapid Response team- Generic Senior Rehabilitation Assistant/ Assistant Practitioners- Band 4&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you an experienced Rehabilitation Assistant who has a passion for patients staying at home, working in an unplanned way and avoiding Hospital Admission where possible?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit experienced Rehabilitation Assistant looking for a new challenge and would like to join our expanding Rapid Response Team in a role that will provide short term rehabilitation interventions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicants will be part of a Multidisciplinary team, passionate about admission prevention.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicants will work alongside Therapist’s and members of the MDT to support the daily work of the rapid response team. As part of the team you will be working with patients who require early/urgent therapy intervention to remain independent within their own home environment and prevent unnecessary hospital admission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rapid Response is a county wide team working as part of the new ‘Somerset Intermediate Care Service’, working alongside the 4 Neighbourhood’s within Somerset. Therapists will be based from either West Mendip/Bridgwater/Dene Barton or South Petherton Community Hospitals, working within a neighbourhood but due to capacity, and staffing issues such as sickness, leave and vacancies a cross country cover will be expected.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Main aims of the service is to&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prevent unnecessary hospital admission&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep service user to their optimal functional level in their own home&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reduce the need for ongoing care and potentially reduce referral on to Discharge to assess service buy using the enablement approach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide support to enable quick turnaround of patients from Hospital to prevent longer hospital stay than is needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Other aspects of this role is to actively link work alongside the JETT team(MPH) and Rapid turnaround team (YDH) and equivalents In RUH and WGH, enhancing the conversation and support positive risk taking to discharge patient back to their own environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To support transition from the service another key aspect of the role will be to have understanding of other community services within the county and build/form relationships with Community teams/Voluntary Sector and Adult Social Care team’s around the county to allow a seamless transition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours of work for this post are between 8 am and 8 pm, 7 days a week. You will be expected to work in shifts during the week alongside to ensure the full day is supported from a therapy point of view.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be an expectation to work alongside the Therapy team to provide training regarding enablement/rehabilitation approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
